&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;Purpose-Driven Work&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;: You will play a crucial role in supporting our clients&#39; recovery journey, contributing to treatment goals, and facilitating individual, group, and family therapy sessions. Your work will have a real impact on the lives of young people and their families.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;201341983&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;Mental Health Nurse&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;(RN OR LPN)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Work Environment/Location:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;Young Adult Residential Treatment Program | Boulder, Colorado&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Type:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;Full Time Day Shift - Thursday to Saturday (6:00am to 6:30pm) &amp;amp; Full Time Overnight Available Tuesday,&lt;span data-teams=&quot;true&quot;&gt; Friday, Saturday (6:00pm- 6:30am) &amp;amp; PRN opportunities available! (12.5 hour shifts)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
